value.0: Talk to Mikel. Him do the business round here...
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 1. >>
We not give you any more trouble...
Death to the Imperial scum!
<StartAction>[The Half-Orc stands silently. It appears he has little to say to you...]</Start>
<StartAction>[The Half-Orc guard appears none too happy to have been detained by Imperial soldiers, and scowls at you.]</Start> Mikel will deal with you, little <man/woman>!
<StartAction>[As you approach, you notice the Half-Orc guarding the door is a large, muscular brute. The massive axe in his hand appears to have seen quite a bit of action in its time...]</Start>
I not have anything to say. You go to Mikel Ravenclaw to talk...
I thought I told you not to come here again! Why you not listen... <StartAction>[Suddenly, the Half-Orc stops in mid sentence, narrowing his eyes at you.]</Start> Wait a minute...
<StartAction>[The large Half-Orc looks at you closely as you come nearer, confusion in his eyes.]</Start> You look familiar, like someone I supposed to look for... What you want?
<StartAction>[The Half-Orc grunts as you turn to depart.]</Start>
<StartAction>[The Half-Orc's eyes grow large.]</Start> The Magistrate's <CUSTOM6001>! You not leave here alive! <StartAction>[The Half-Orc yells a warning, and rushes to attack.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> I could buy that shiny new axe with some extra gold... Alright, you give me 50 gold, I let you pass.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> You not turn me against Mikel for petty amount of gold! You not pass through these doors!
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> I could buy new boots with gold! Alright, you give me 20 gold, I let you pass.
<StartAction>[The Half-Orc's eyes flare in anger.]</Start> I tired of your games, foolish <Class>!
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> You not scare me! Now get out of here before I slash you up!
<StartAction>[Success] [The Half-Orc glances you over, and seems to think better of refusing your request.]</Start> Alright, you pass. But don't try nothing foolish, or we cut you to pieces!
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> I not remember you! You not fool me! Get out of here!
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> <StartAction>[The Half-Orc scratches his head in confusion.]</Start> Maybe so. Alright, you can pass, but you not try anything foolish!
<StartAction>[The Half-Orc motions for you to enter through the door behind him.]</Start>
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> <StartAction>[The Half-Orc guard looks over you, a look of disgust coming over his face.]</Start> Mikel Ravenclaw not have anything to do with woman as ugly as you!
I not want to see you around here again! Get out! <StartAction>[The fierce rage in the Half-Orc's eyes leads you to believe it would be unwise to speak with him again.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> Mikel pick pretty one this time. Alright, woman, you can pass.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Me not informed of anyone coming for business! You not fool me! Get out of here!
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> You seem like friend to me. You can go through, but you make sure to behave!
This door off limits! You not pass through here!
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 0. >>

Just passing by. I'll be on my way.
I am <FullName>! Your master has plotted against me, and now I come for his death!
<StartAction>[Bribe]</Start> Would 50 gold pieces be enough to convince you to let me pass?
<StartAction>[Hand over the gold.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Bribe.]</Start> Would you be willing to let me pass for, say, 20 gold pieces?
On second thought, I don't think I'm willing to part with my gold...
<StartAction>[Hand over the gold.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Intimidation]</Start> Let me pass, you oafish brute, or you will regret it!
<StartAction>[Persuade]</Start> I have been here before, on business with Mikel Ravenclaw. Don't you remember me?
<StartAction>[Persuade]</Start> I am a dancer come to perform for Mikel's entertainment. Surely a gentleman such as yourself would not deny my entrance...
I have business with Mikel. Can I please pass?
